author: TALKERS
title: SRN Launches Texas Disaster Relief Effort
text: Salem Radio Network is partnering with international non-profit relief agency Food for the Poor to rush emergency relief kits to flood-ravaged Texas. SRN talk hosts Mike Gallagher , Chris Stigall , Hugh Hewitt , and Larry Elder are supporting this campaign on their programs. SRN vice president/news & talk programming Tom Tradup says Food for the Poor‚Äôs ‚Äúdecades of providing disaster relief throughout our hemisphere which ‚Äì in coordination with trusted partners in San Antonio ‚Äì will assure swift, professional response to communities affected by Central Texas flooding.‚Äù

author: CNN Newsource
title: Bible study behind bars with ‚ÄòPastor Bob‚Äô
text:
Bible study behind bars with ‚ÄòPastor Bob‚Äô
Click here for updates on this story
SALT LAKE CITY, Utah (
KSTU) ‚Äî Prison can be a dark, cold and lonely place.
It‚Äôs a place most people want to avoid.
But for more than 30 years, Robert Aguilar walked through the gates of the Utah State Prison willingly in an effort to deliver hope.
‚ÄúGod has listened and heard my voice in prayer,‚Äù Aguilar reads from scripture.
The tools of the trade are simple. A kind voice, an open heart, and a Bible.
‚ÄúThere is a dark area of the prison system and some get tired of it,‚Äù Aguilar said. ‚ÄúThey want to change and that means it‚Äôs from the heart.‚Äù
Aguilar began taking his Bible to the Utah State Prison in 1983. It was a way for him to turn his life around.
‚ÄúI had a sense of worthlessness because of the life I had been leading previously,‚Äù Aguilar said. ‚ÄúI was a heavy drinker. My wife mentioned that she was going to leave me.‚Äù
Faith, Aguilar says, changed his life.
‚ÄúI felt like I had something more. We all have something in our lives that calls to that. There is something more important that we can do than just living.‚Äù
It was that faith that led Aguilar to devote his Sunday mornings as a christian minister ‚Äî volunteering with prisoners willing to listen.
‚ÄúWhen I walk in they call me ‚ÄòPastor Bob,‚Äô they all know me as Pastor Bob here.
Bryan Taylor is a deputy warden for the prison who oversees volunteers.
‚ÄúI actually reached out and talked to some of the inmates out of the prison and they just love him,‚Äù Taylor said.
The deputy warden says the service provided by Aguilar and prison volunteers is life changing.
‚ÄúIndividuals when they are locked away and they are contemplating their life ‚Äì having someone to talk to ‚Äì that one-on-one communication face-to-face can not be replicated by anything else than doing it,‚Äù Taylor said.
Now 88 years old, Aguilar likes to be with his family, work in his garden, or enjoy a meal at Ogies, his favorite restaurant in West Valley City. It‚Äôs a place where he‚Äôs reconnected with some former prisoners.
‚ÄúI had fellows come in and they tapped me on the back and they say ‚ÄòPastor Bob, you don‚Äôt know me, I was in your services and I took on what you told me, what was in scripture that my life could be changed. My life has changed I go to church and I am a happy man and I want to thank you for what you did.‚Äô‚Äù
Those moments bring Aguilar joy, knowing his change for the good has helped others find a similar path and bring good to the world.
‚ÄúPraise be to God who has not rejected my prayer or has not held his love from me.‚Äù
Aguilar says he would have liked to keep going, but the walk in the new prison parking lot is just too much compared to the old facility. He estimates the walk is about a quarter of a mile and he‚Äôs afraid he‚Äôd fall down and hurt himself.
Still though, prisoners call him on the phone to maintain communication.
If you‚Äôre interested in being a volunteer at the Utah State Prison, here is a link:
corrections.utah.gov/volunteer/volunteer-programs

author: Jason Owens, Yahoo Sports
title: Ja'Marr Chase pokes Kansas City secondary ahead of Bengals-Chiefs game: 'They can't do it 1 on 1' ‚Äì Boston 25 News
text:
By Jason Owens, Yahoo Sports December 28, 2023 at 6:52 pm EST
Expand
AFC Championship - Cincinnati Bengals v Kansas City Chiefs KANSAS CITY, MISSOURI - JANUARY 29: Ja'Marr Chase #1 of the Cincinnati Bengals reacts as he celebrates completing a pass during the AFC Championship NFL football game between the Kansas City Chiefs and the Cincinnati Bengals at GEHA Field at Arrowhead Stadium on January 29, 2023 in Kansas City, Missouri. (Photo by Michael Owens/Getty Images) (Michael Owens/Getty Images)
By Jason Owens, Yahoo Sports December 28, 2023 at 6:52 pm EST The Cincinnati Bengals and Kansas City Chiefs have beef fueled by high-stakes battles in a split of the last two AFC championship games.
The 2023 stakes are muted thanks to Joe Burrow's season-ending wrist injury. But that's not stopping Ja'Marr Chase from adding "fire to the fuel" ahead of Sunday's game. The All-Pro Bengals receiver went out of his way on Thursday to take shots at the Kansas City defense.
"I know what I see on paper. I know what I see in game," Chase told reporters of the Chiefs defense. "That's why they double everybody. 'Cause they can't do it one on one.
"The best player on their team is [cornerback L'Jarius] Sneed. That's a fact. Everybody knows that. That's why they double everything they see. ... They know I'm good. They know how to play us. It's not like they've got a superstar on their defense."
Ja‚ÄôMarr Chase didn‚Äôt back track at all when asked about his assessment of Chiefs defense. ‚ÄúThey can take it how they want. I don‚Äôt care. ‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm not Ironman. I can‚Äôt throw the ball to myself. It‚Äôs a team sport.‚Äù pic.twitter.com/KmnaKIcLYe
‚Äî Mike Petraglia (@Trags) December 28, 2023 Neither Sneed nor Chase are sure to play on Sunday. Sneed's been sidelined at practice this week with a calf strain. Chase has been limited by a lingering shoulder injury that sidelined him last week. But he sounds ready to challenge the Kansas City secondary if he can go with no concern for providing bulletin-board material.
"I'm just adding fire to the fuel right now," Chase continued. "They're gonna take this, run with it. Hope they put it in their locker."
At 9-6, this is not a vintage Chiefs team. They're seeking to clinch the AFC West on Sunday after blowing an opportunity to do so in a stunning Christmas Day loss to the Las Vegas Raiders. But their defense is excellent. Kansas City enters Week 17 ranked second in total defense and third against the pass. Chase is poking a quite capable bear.
He also has the receipts to back up his talk. Chase has made the Pro Bowl in each of his two NFL seasons and posted a career game with 266 yards and three touchdowns in 2021 against Kansas City. The 8-7 Bengals will need him Sunday as they fight to keep their dwindling playoff hopes alive.
